<label></label>
================
1)a piece of paper, etc. that is fixed to something and which gives information about it.
2)Screen reader users  (will read out loud the label, when the user is focused on the element)

3)Users who have difficulty clicking on very small regions (such as checkboxes) - because 
                 when a user clicks the text within the <label> element, it toggles the input (this increases the hit area). 

4)Why clicking the label does NOT select the radio button?
Because for in <label> is NOT connected to any input id.